main event: A civilian observer reported seeing an unidentified flying object near Honolulu, Hawaii on November 26, 1964.
interesting points: The object appeared to be motionless and hovering between 500-600 feet in the air.
The object was described as an elliptically shaped, dark-colored object with no sound.
The object appeared to maneuver and gain altitude, moving against the direction of the winds.
The observer had detailed knowledge of aircraft and air force operations, and could not identify the object.
The observer provided a rough sketch of the object, depicting a disc-shaped and mushroom-shaped form.
witnesses: Civilian observer, Carl R. Nagatori and his wife
photographs: No photographs, only a sketch provided
